column5: Here are some pics from Tony's phone. He was fishing a little ways away in his comfy hut lol        Tony got one into the teens
Great report Aaron.  Yes,broiled is so much healthier and better tasting IMO.  TFS
damn, that's one productive day...I think you guys caught more lakers/whitefish than I did perch on my outting
Nice report! Thanks for sharing Aaron!

Small world Aaron.  We were set up closer to shore than you guys. Had I've known it was you and Tony, I would have popped out to say "Hi". Some of those pressure cracks opened up and shifting when we got off the ice. The scariest moment was when my buddy was ahead of me by about 60 ft. The ice cracked and shifted about 14 inches. I should have taken a picture of it as you could see the shift by his sled tracks and foot prints. we got a late start but did put a hurten on lakers and a few whities.  When did you start doning the beard and stache?  Cheers, Ron....

Aaron.............I  am so happy for u guys and so jealous at the same time.......we lived 3 miles from where u were fishing for 18 years,,,,,,,,,fished those grounds 100s of times , miss those whitefish,,,,,,,,,,mmmmmmmmmm  good,  might have to fly back and have a day with yourselves, those are days u never forget. Good 4 you and look forward to more great reports.  Cheers Blizz
Great stuff Aaron. simcoe seems to be a fish factory!
Nice fish!   Can't wait to make up for last year myself.
Nice! Can't wait to get up there
Great report! It was definitely a zoo out there.
